WEBVTT

00:00.255 --> 00:01.955
<i>Previously on
"One Tree Hill"...</i>

00:01.956 --> 00:03.415
Clay: I don't know
what's happening to me.

00:03.416 --> 00:04.916
I was so worried.

00:06.185 --> 00:08.953
Dad,
how would you feel...

00:09.021 --> 00:10.521
If we included mom?

00:10.589 --> 00:12.757
You know, I think
your mother had her chance...

00:12.824 --> 00:14.391
And she betrayed
your trust.

00:14.459 --> 00:17.361
I want you to live here...
Because I love you.

00:17.429 --> 00:19.030
I want to take that tour.

00:20.699 --> 00:25.401
Julian: The movie that was going
to rent our stage fell through.

00:25.469 --> 00:28.038
Haley: I'm gonna go meet the guy
that's gonna run red bedroom.

00:28.105 --> 00:30.640
Well, well.

00:30.708 --> 00:32.809
I come home to find
my father holding Lydia.

00:32.877 --> 00:34.578
But he said
his diner burned down,

00:34.645 --> 00:36.245
and we were
standing in a church.

00:36.280 --> 00:37.780
Dan has to go.

00:39.000 --> 00:45.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

00:46.557 --> 00:48.891
[ Dawes' "if I wanted someone"
plays ]

01:04.607 --> 01:07.242
♪ Like the memory
from your mother's house ♪

01:07.310 --> 01:10.445
♪ from before
you got too old ♪

01:10.513 --> 01:13.514
♪ like the feeling
from a photograph ♪

01:13.582 --> 01:16.783
♪ before its meanings
all got told ♪

01:16.851 --> 01:19.120
♪ the words I say
can be silver... ♪

01:19.187 --> 01:20.988
Clay?

01:21.055 --> 01:22.789
Clay!

01:22.857 --> 01:25.626
♪ So get to know me
once I go away ♪

01:25.693 --> 01:26.994
Hey.

01:26.995 --> 01:28.394
Look who decided to join
the land of the living.

01:28.395 --> 01:29.629
Yeah, you just, uh,

01:29.630 --> 01:31.598
you weren't in bed,
and I got scared.

01:31.665 --> 01:33.165
Thought it happened again.

01:33.200 --> 01:35.201
Oh, I'm sorry.
I didn't mean to scare you.

01:35.269 --> 01:37.170
It's just been
a rough couple of weeks,

01:37.238 --> 01:38.738
so I thought
I'd surprise you

01:38.772 --> 01:40.906
with my famous Clay deluxe
breakfast in bed.

01:40.974 --> 01:42.975
Didn't know you had
a famous breakfast.

01:43.043 --> 01:44.576
Yeah, it's not really
famous yet.

01:44.644 --> 01:47.212
Extensive bragging on your end
was part of the plan.

01:47.280 --> 01:50.449
Hey, I even left out
the crossword puzzle for you

01:50.483 --> 01:53.918
and your chewed-up, kind of
awesome, kind of gross pen.

01:55.588 --> 01:58.056
You're kind of awesome
and kind of gross.

02:01.527 --> 02:03.294
Way more awesome
than gross.

02:03.362 --> 02:04.295
I'll take it.

02:04.296 --> 02:05.329
Now get back to bed.

02:05.330 --> 02:07.365
I'd rather watch you
in action.

02:07.432 --> 02:09.900
♪ If I wanted someone
to understand me ♪

02:09.967 --> 02:12.170
♪ I'd have
so much more to say ♪

02:12.237 --> 02:14.639
♪ I want you to make
the days move easy ♪

02:14.706 --> 02:16.106
Here you girls,
girls.

02:16.107 --> 02:18.341
I'll get you some
cream cheese for that.

02:18.442 --> 02:20.810
Hi, I... I'm just
gonna be one minute.

02:20.878 --> 02:23.680
I'll have your table.
I'm sorry about the wait.

02:23.714 --> 02:25.848
Table 1 needs an iced mocha
and a hot tea,

02:25.916 --> 02:27.050
table 5,
toasted bagel,

02:27.051 --> 02:28.451
and the ACLU wants to know

02:28.452 --> 02:30.320
why you're violating
child labor laws.

02:30.388 --> 02:31.655
Yeah, very funny.

02:31.656 --> 02:33.422
Since when did we start
numbering tables?

02:33.490 --> 02:34.756
Uh,
about an hour ago.

02:34.757 --> 02:35.957
It's way too busy
not to.

02:35.958 --> 02:37.959
Hi, it's Haley.

02:37.994 --> 02:42.698
Yeah, I'm just wondering
where you are.

02:42.765 --> 02:44.700
You what?

02:44.834 --> 02:46.569
No,
you can't do that!

02:46.636 --> 02:47.803
I need to...

02:47.804 --> 02:49.537
Well,
to heck with you, too.

02:49.605 --> 02:51.372
She's just kidding,
folks.

02:51.440 --> 02:54.309
And coffee's on the house
this morning.

02:54.376 --> 02:56.711
Well, our no-show chef
just quit.

02:56.778 --> 02:58.913
Chef Jeff?
Aw, that's too bad.

02:58.980 --> 03:00.315
I like saying,
"chef Jeff."

03:00.316 --> 03:03.117
Chef Jeff. Chef Jeff.

03:03.185 --> 03:05.819
Oh, maybe it has something
to do with this.

03:05.886 --> 03:08.655
♪ If I wanted someone
to spend my money ♪

03:08.723 --> 03:11.258
♪ I wouldn't need to
get paid ♪

03:11.326 --> 03:14.928
♪ if I wanted someone
to understand me ♪

03:14.995 --> 03:17.197
♪ I'd have
so much more to say ♪

03:17.265 --> 03:19.099
[ Gasps ] No!
Yeah.

03:19.166 --> 03:22.835
♪ I want you to make
the days move easy ♪

03:22.902 --> 03:26.539
♪ I just want you to make
the days move easy ♪

03:26.607 --> 03:30.576
[ Mutters ]
Our food is gourmet.

03:30.644 --> 03:31.777
Right?

03:31.778 --> 03:33.278
Oh, yeah.

03:37.250 --> 03:40.252
Go-o-o-o-o-al!

03:40.319 --> 03:43.555
Putt-putt skills don't translate
onto a real golf course.

03:43.623 --> 03:46.023
Oh, whatever.
I'm totally bogeying down.

03:46.091 --> 03:46.924
Get it?

03:46.925 --> 03:48.360
Yeah, I get it.

03:48.361 --> 03:50.228
Don't expect your father
to laugh, though.

03:50.296 --> 03:52.029
He takes golf
very seriously,

03:52.097 --> 03:54.331
and you want a birdie
more than you want a bogey.

03:54.399 --> 03:55.699
I know.

03:55.700 --> 03:57.668
I just remember
when I was a kid,

03:57.736 --> 04:00.036
daddy spent every weekend
playing golf

04:00.104 --> 04:02.439
with all those important
business people.

04:02.507 --> 04:04.074
Don't remind me.

04:04.142 --> 04:08.711
I spent 20 mind-numbing years
as that man's golf widow.

04:08.779 --> 04:11.981
Well, now <i>I</i> get to hang out
with him today and play golf,

04:12.048 --> 04:13.949
so what else
do I need to know?

04:14.017 --> 04:15.517
Is that
what you're wearing?

04:17.053 --> 04:18.321
What?

04:18.322 --> 04:21.257
Mm. It's cute.
You'll be fine.

04:21.325 --> 04:22.825
What?

04:24.127 --> 04:27.329
Honey, look, I know
you've made up your mind

04:27.397 --> 04:29.030
about going into business
with your father.

04:29.098 --> 04:32.334
All I ask is that
you be careful, okay?

04:32.402 --> 04:34.770
I love you, and I don't want to
see you get hurt.

04:34.837 --> 04:36.171
That's all.

04:36.172 --> 04:39.073
Really?

04:39.141 --> 04:40.641
That's all?

04:41.810 --> 04:46.013
Well, I'd prefer you ban him
from picking up my grandsons.

04:46.080 --> 04:47.782
But you can't have it all.

04:51.753 --> 04:54.221
Hey, he feels
just a little warm.

04:54.289 --> 04:55.723
Will you watch him today

04:55.724 --> 04:57.424
and take his temperature
if he gets any warmer?

04:57.491 --> 04:59.025
Mm-hmm.

04:59.092 --> 05:00.427
Okay.

05:00.428 --> 05:03.162
Julian will be home after lunch
to relieve you.

05:03.230 --> 05:04.631
He's working

05:04.632 --> 05:08.301
and then giving Jamie's class
a tour of the sound stage.

05:08.369 --> 05:09.636
Did he finally figure out

05:09.637 --> 05:11.204
something to do with
that dreadful warehouse?

05:11.271 --> 05:14.473
You know, people in town,
they're...Talking.

05:16.609 --> 05:18.076
Bye, mother.

05:18.077 --> 05:20.646
She's okay.
She'll be back.

05:23.450 --> 05:24.883
[ Coos ]

05:24.884 --> 05:27.419
We have state-of-the-art
facilities and a great area.

05:27.487 --> 05:29.320
Tree Hill
has a historic downtown,

05:29.388 --> 05:32.289
the beach, great locations,
you name it.

05:32.358 --> 05:34.692
Did I mention
the tax incentive?

05:34.760 --> 05:36.260
I did?

05:38.597 --> 05:41.833
Uh, sure.
I understand.

05:41.900 --> 05:44.901
Okay, well, keep is in mind
for future projects.

05:44.969 --> 05:46.370
Okay. Thanks again.

05:46.371 --> 05:50.874
♪ Staring out the window,
the moon is in disguise ♪

05:50.941 --> 05:54.911
♪ it's the soft light luminates her eyes ♪
Ellen O'Sullivan, please.

05:54.979 --> 05:58.882
♪ She's the face of someone that I
could get lost in ♪ Yes. I will hold.

06:01.951 --> 06:05.688
Hey, Lisa,
the table over there...

06:05.756 --> 06:07.523
♪ And so it goes ♪

06:07.591 --> 06:08.691
Oh, Chase!

06:08.692 --> 06:09.792
Sorry!

06:09.793 --> 06:11.761
I'm having a really crappy
morning.

06:11.828 --> 06:13.161
What can I get you?

06:13.162 --> 06:13.929
I don't know.

06:13.930 --> 06:15.698
I haven't eaten in days.

06:15.766 --> 06:17.532
Haven't really slept,
either.

06:17.600 --> 06:19.100
Alex?

06:20.870 --> 06:23.438
I'm really sorry.
I know you liked her a lot.

06:23.506 --> 06:25.807
Yeah, well, I'll be sure
to thank Chris Keller

06:25.875 --> 06:27.108
next time I see him.

06:27.109 --> 06:29.210
Trust me.

06:29.278 --> 06:32.213
I know Chris Keller is not good
for relationships.

06:32.281 --> 06:35.716
And chit-chatting on the job
is bad for business.

06:35.784 --> 06:38.852
You know, um, you really should
try and eat something.

06:38.920 --> 06:40.387
Try not to think
about Alex.

06:40.388 --> 06:42.823
Definitely put the thought of
Chris Keller out of your mind.

06:46.728 --> 06:48.895
[ Sighs ]Chuck Skolnick is starving.

06:52.399 --> 06:53.899
Hey.

06:59.005 --> 07:00.306
Excuse me.

07:00.307 --> 07:03.242
Hi, I'm here to interview
for the internship.

07:03.310 --> 07:04.810
Wrong office.

07:04.811 --> 07:07.045
Oh.
Okay. Sorry.

07:10.883 --> 07:12.383
Wait, wait, wait.

07:13.653 --> 07:17.121
Uh, how much
is this internship paying?

07:17.189 --> 07:18.457
Nothing.

07:18.458 --> 07:20.591
It's an internship,
so I work for free.

07:20.659 --> 07:22.426
Wait, wait, wait.
Sorry, sorry.

07:22.494 --> 07:24.027
Uh, let me
get this straight.

07:24.095 --> 07:25.830
You show up,
looking like that...

07:25.897 --> 07:28.031
which is really sexy,
by the way...

07:28.099 --> 07:29.900
and you work for free?

07:29.968 --> 07:32.035
Mm-hmm.

07:32.103 --> 07:34.538
And what exactly
do you do?

07:34.606 --> 07:37.340
Whatever
they tell me to do.

07:37.407 --> 07:38.741
[ Jocelyn Alice's "imposter"
plays ]

07:38.742 --> 07:40.477
[ Chuckles ]

07:40.544 --> 07:43.179
Tell me why you want to work
at red bedroom records.

07:43.246 --> 07:45.682
I am a big fan
of hip-hop.

07:45.749 --> 07:48.650
Fantastic.
We do hip-hop.

07:48.718 --> 07:51.854
I'm really into techno...
deep house.

07:51.921 --> 07:54.890
I-I <i>love</i> the deep house.

07:54.958 --> 07:56.825
♪ That's what you're doin'
to me ♪

07:56.893 --> 07:58.393
Well,
I love country music.

07:58.395 --> 08:00.762
Yeah, we don't do
country music here.

08:00.830 --> 08:02.330
But Alex Dupré...

08:02.331 --> 08:03.831
yeah, that was...
that was just...

08:03.866 --> 08:05.333
let me give you
a parting gift.

08:05.334 --> 08:06.834
♪ I was hoping
you'd hear me out ♪

08:06.902 --> 08:09.904
♪ but the shouts
are drowning me ♪

08:09.972 --> 08:12.507
Yeah.

08:12.574 --> 08:14.009
There you go.

08:14.010 --> 08:16.177
♪ You'd see the sound,
but you're too damn weak ♪

08:16.245 --> 08:18.112
You're welcome.

08:18.179 --> 08:19.213
I'm sorry.

08:19.214 --> 08:20.414
I was under
the impression

08:20.415 --> 08:22.082
I was interviewing
for an internship,

08:22.150 --> 08:23.884
but the post said
to bring a bikini.

08:23.951 --> 08:26.553
Yeah, occasionally, we do
our own video shoots here.

08:26.621 --> 08:28.188
We might need you
as an extra.

08:28.256 --> 08:29.656
Did you...
Bring the bikini?

08:29.657 --> 08:31.157
No.

08:33.227 --> 08:34.860
But I have a bra on.
Will that work?

08:35.895 --> 08:37.696
That'll do just fine.

08:37.764 --> 08:40.765
To be honest,
we don't even like music.

08:40.833 --> 08:42.068
We hate it.

08:42.068 --> 08:44.970
That's fine.
When can you guys start?

08:45.039 --> 08:46.539
I guess now,
if you want.

08:46.573 --> 08:48.174
Perfect.

08:48.242 --> 08:50.042
What do you
want us to do?

08:50.109 --> 08:51.410
I don't know.

08:51.411 --> 08:53.945
Bend, stretch, just sit here
and look pretty.

08:54.013 --> 08:56.014
I'm gonna grab
some breakfast.

08:56.082 --> 08:57.882
Should I answer
the phone?

08:57.950 --> 08:59.817
Oh! Answer the phone.
Good call.

09:00.886 --> 09:02.554
♪ I gotta get gone ♪

09:02.621 --> 09:05.290
"Harness for oxen."

09:05.358 --> 09:06.590
Yoke.

09:06.591 --> 09:08.292
[ Cellphone rings ]

09:08.360 --> 09:10.461
Hey,
can you get that?

09:10.529 --> 09:11.795
Hello?

09:11.796 --> 09:13.730
Woman:
<i>This is Tree Hill pharmacy</i>

09:13.798 --> 09:17.068
<i>reminding you that your</i>
<i>prescription is ready.</i>

09:17.135 --> 09:20.271
<i>Your prescription will be</i>
<i>available for pick-up</i>

09:20.338 --> 09:21.672
<i>for two more days.</i>

09:21.673 --> 09:22.772
[ Cellphone clicks ]

09:22.773 --> 09:25.108
Who was it?

09:25.176 --> 09:26.576
Wrong number.

09:26.577 --> 09:29.512
Good, 'cause I am starving
and breakfast is ready.

09:29.580 --> 09:32.549
Madam, I present
the Clay deluxe.

09:32.616 --> 09:33.783
[ Laughs ]

09:33.784 --> 09:36.486
Just what the doctor
ordered.

09:36.554 --> 09:37.920
That reminds me...

09:37.921 --> 09:40.822
did you pick up
your prescription last week?

09:40.890 --> 09:42.657
Mm-hmm.
Hey, new tradition...

09:42.725 --> 09:44.859
every Saturday should start
with a Clay deluxe.

09:46.929 --> 09:48.530
So, you've been taking
your pills every day?

09:50.766 --> 09:52.867
And they seem like
they're working?

09:52.935 --> 09:54.702
I'm here, aren't I?

09:57.172 --> 09:58.672
Sucker.

10:06.016 --> 10:07.016
Haley, he basically
lied to my face.

10:07.017 --> 10:08.517
He agreed the prescription
was working,

10:08.586 --> 10:10.152
but he never even
picked it up.

10:10.220 --> 10:12.321
That just sounds like
a misunderstanding, though.

10:12.389 --> 10:13.957
There's got to be
a good explanation, Quinn.

10:14.024 --> 10:17.660
Or maybe he's
cheating on you.

10:17.728 --> 10:19.862
What? I'm just saying
if I had a dime

10:19.930 --> 10:22.465
for every time I woke up
on a merry-go-round

10:22.532 --> 10:24.165
or in a park,
I'd be rich.

10:24.233 --> 10:26.167
Do you know what I was doing
every time

10:26.235 --> 10:29.404
right before I woke up
in those places?

10:29.472 --> 10:31.006
Some random chick.

10:31.074 --> 10:34.175
I don't think we've met.
Chris Keller.

10:34.243 --> 10:36.277
Oh, Chris Keller.

10:36.345 --> 10:37.813
Mm.

10:37.814 --> 10:41.348
Quinn James.

10:41.416 --> 10:42.984
Well, well.
[ Sniffs ]

10:43.051 --> 10:44.218
Haley's sister.

10:44.219 --> 10:47.021
Well, it's...
it's always been a fantasy.

10:47.089 --> 10:49.256
Don't shake his hand.
You don't know where it's been.

10:49.324 --> 10:50.424
Come on.

10:50.425 --> 10:51.859
You know where this hand
has been.

10:51.860 --> 10:54.728
But what we don't know is what
your boyfriend's been up to.

10:54.795 --> 10:58.231
Quinn, listen to me.
You know that Clay loves you.

10:58.298 --> 10:59.633
We should GPS his phone,

10:59.634 --> 11:01.901
find out exactly where he's been
sneaking off to.

11:01.969 --> 11:03.637
That's what Chris Keller
would do.

11:03.704 --> 11:06.272
If you need a shoulder
to cry on or...Whatever,

11:06.340 --> 11:10.010
just some revenge sex,
I'm your guy.

11:16.516 --> 11:18.016
Hey, just reminding you,

11:18.051 --> 11:20.653
we have that chef's tasting
at Lisa's later today.

11:20.720 --> 11:21.920
Another tasting?

11:21.921 --> 11:23.722
That's every night
this week.

11:23.790 --> 11:25.858
Well, the audience
loves that segment.

11:25.925 --> 11:26.625
Ugh.

11:26.626 --> 11:28.192
What's wrong?

11:28.260 --> 11:30.528
The stupid dry cleaner
shrunk another shirt.

11:30.595 --> 11:31.929
What is that,
three now?

11:31.930 --> 11:34.198
We should do an exposé
on the dry cleaner.

11:34.266 --> 11:36.200
Someone needs to put a stop
to this.

11:36.268 --> 11:37.702
Haley: Oh, thank God
you're here.

11:37.703 --> 11:38.770
Our chef just quit.

11:38.771 --> 11:40.271
Well, he got poached,
actually,

11:40.272 --> 11:42.206
and I really need you
to grab an apron.

11:42.274 --> 11:44.440
I can't. I have a golf date
with my dad.

11:44.508 --> 11:46.442
I just came to get a muffin
and a coffee.

11:46.510 --> 11:47.477
I'm carbo-loading.

11:47.478 --> 11:48.611
We are swamped.

11:48.612 --> 11:50.413
Wh... [ Sighs ]
Okay. I can help.

11:50.481 --> 11:52.049
That means a lot.
Thank you.

11:52.116 --> 11:53.616
Sure. I'll make
my own coffee.

11:55.553 --> 11:56.820
Who are we kidding?

11:56.821 --> 11:58.621
I still don't know
how to use that thing.

11:58.689 --> 11:59.789
Would you mind?

11:59.790 --> 12:02.524
Please?
You're so good at it.

12:02.592 --> 12:06.028
You excited about your field
trip to Julian's sound stage?

12:06.096 --> 12:07.596
Chuck?

12:11.968 --> 12:16.037
Well, well.

12:16.105 --> 12:18.406
I told you not to tell Alex
her music was crap.

12:18.473 --> 12:19.808
Crappy.

12:19.809 --> 12:21.275
So, you send her on tour
instead?

12:21.276 --> 12:22.310
What's your problem,
man?

12:22.311 --> 12:23.845
You know what?

12:23.913 --> 12:26.514
It doesn't even matter.
You're just a...

12:28.184 --> 12:31.585
not very nice person.

12:33.722 --> 12:35.622
Contrary
to popular opinion,

12:35.690 --> 12:37.825
he doesn't speak
for the both of us.

12:39.427 --> 12:41.328
You got
a good look, kid.

12:41.395 --> 12:43.230
Bet the honeys love you.

12:43.297 --> 12:46.233
Uh...Totally.
[ Chuckles ]

12:46.300 --> 12:47.934
Here.

12:48.001 --> 12:49.501
Wear this.

12:50.204 --> 12:51.503
[ Knock on door ]

12:51.504 --> 12:53.505
Get your butt out here,
Skolnick.

12:54.842 --> 12:56.342
See you around,
Chris Keller.

12:56.409 --> 12:58.044
All right.
See you, buddy.

13:25.070 --> 13:26.536
Nathan: All right, and I
appreciate the way you've been

13:26.537 --> 13:27.838
with my wife and my family,

13:27.839 --> 13:30.407
but when I come back,
you need to be gone.

13:30.475 --> 13:32.009
Make your plans and go.

13:32.077 --> 13:34.378
Don't say that.
Never say that.

13:34.445 --> 13:35.945
Goonies never say die.

13:39.250 --> 13:42.318
I'm not a goonie.
I want to go home.

13:43.821 --> 13:45.755
But don't you realize

13:45.823 --> 13:50.326
the next time you see sky,
it'll be over another town?

13:50.394 --> 13:52.027
The next time
you take a test,

13:52.095 --> 13:55.130
it'll be in
some other school.

13:55.198 --> 13:58.400
Our parents, they want
the bestest stuff for us,

13:58.467 --> 14:01.670
but right now, they got to do
what's right for them

14:01.737 --> 14:03.305
because it's their time...

14:03.372 --> 14:04.872
their time up there.

14:04.908 --> 14:10.611
Down here, it's our time...
our time down here!

14:10.679 --> 14:14.816
That's all over the second
we ride up Troy's bucket.

14:14.883 --> 14:16.383
[ Clears throat ]
Hey, Julian?

14:17.786 --> 14:20.421
The field trip was scheduled
for today, right?

14:22.390 --> 14:24.357
Hi, Julia.

14:24.425 --> 14:26.293
[ Laughs ]

14:28.629 --> 14:31.298
Who do I need to screw to get
a burger around here?

14:31.365 --> 14:32.665
Please let it be you.

14:32.666 --> 14:33.900
You ordered a burger?

14:33.901 --> 14:36.236
No. Originally, I ordered
a breakfast burrito.

14:36.304 --> 14:37.770
We don't serve those
after 11:00.

14:37.771 --> 14:40.172
Well, you did an hour ago
when I ordered it,

14:40.240 --> 14:43.075
but seeing as it's lunchtime,
you can get me a burger.

14:43.143 --> 14:44.643
Come with me.

14:46.779 --> 14:48.747
Lunchtime quickie.
Nice!

14:48.815 --> 14:51.583
Hey, uh, few more minutes
on your burgers, folks.

14:51.684 --> 14:53.218
Like seven minutes.

14:53.285 --> 14:56.655
♪ You've been far away from me... ♪
Put this on.

14:56.723 --> 14:58.490
You can cook, right?

14:58.558 --> 15:01.059
Chris Keller
can do it all, baby.

15:01.126 --> 15:04.795
♪ Just waiting 'round and aching
for a letter or a telegram... ♪

15:04.863 --> 15:07.865
[ High-pitched voice ]Aah! Aaaah!

15:07.932 --> 15:09.432
Aaah!

15:09.434 --> 15:11.168
Aaah!

15:11.236 --> 15:12.302
Aah!

15:12.303 --> 15:15.205
Calm down.
Give me this.

15:15.273 --> 15:17.274
♪ Till you're
standing right here ♪

15:17.342 --> 15:20.009
♪ next to the one
who adores you ♪

15:20.077 --> 15:22.178
♪ whose heart is beating
for you ♪

15:22.246 --> 15:24.848
♪ like the lighthouse guides
a shipwrecked sailor ♪

15:24.915 --> 15:26.549
♪ safely from the sea ♪

15:26.617 --> 15:31.488
♪ I'll wear your colors
till you come back home to me ♪

15:33.624 --> 15:36.358
♪ I'm hoping
you return the glow ♪

15:36.426 --> 15:37.225
♪ I'm just making sure... ♪

15:37.226 --> 15:39.795
Excuse me.

15:39.863 --> 15:41.263
Perfect timing.
We just finished.

15:41.264 --> 15:43.098
Come join us for lunch.

15:43.165 --> 15:44.165
"Us"?

15:44.166 --> 15:45.567
Potential investors.

15:45.568 --> 15:47.703
They're very excited
to meet you.

15:47.771 --> 15:50.071
I don't understand.
You already played golf?

15:50.139 --> 15:52.507
Yes, but those clubs
are a nice touch, Brookie.

15:52.574 --> 15:54.675
But I...

15:54.743 --> 15:56.477
if you didn't want to
play golf with me,

15:56.545 --> 15:57.678
why am I here?

15:57.679 --> 15:59.113
I warm them up
with a round of golf,

15:59.114 --> 16:00.915
and you charm them
with a fabulous lunch.

16:00.982 --> 16:01.883
Okay.

16:01.884 --> 16:03.384
Here she is.

16:03.419 --> 16:07.454
Gentlemen, my daughter,
<i>the</i> Brooke Davis.

16:07.522 --> 16:08.922
Thanks.

16:08.923 --> 16:10.690
Greg.
It's good to meet you.

16:10.758 --> 16:11.691
Hello.

16:11.692 --> 16:12.992
Peter.
Hello.

16:12.993 --> 16:14.493
Hi.

16:24.337 --> 16:25.838
You know, is it just me,

16:25.906 --> 16:28.373
or are shirts being cut
smaller these days?

16:28.442 --> 16:29.575
It's called "slim fit."

16:29.576 --> 16:31.076
People like their shirts
tailored.

16:31.077 --> 16:32.577
Yeah, well,
slim fit or not,

16:32.579 --> 16:35.314
my dry cleaner keeps
shrinking my shirts.

16:35.381 --> 16:37.750
They have one job to do,
and that's clean my shirts,

16:37.818 --> 16:39.851
not clean them
and then shrink them.

16:39.919 --> 16:42.086
[ Chuckling ] You know, if I wanted to
shrink them, I'd have Millie wash them.

16:42.154 --> 16:43.321
[ Chuckles ]

16:43.322 --> 16:46.057
I don't think
you should go there.

16:46.124 --> 16:48.192
Well, I'm just saying,
of your many talents,

16:48.260 --> 16:49.994
laundry is definitely
not one of them.

16:52.665 --> 16:54.365
You've been shrinking
my shirts, haven't you?

16:54.433 --> 16:55.632
You know what?
It's okay.

16:55.633 --> 16:56.900
You'll feel better
when you admit it.

16:56.901 --> 16:57.801
Go ahead.
No, Marvin.

16:57.802 --> 16:59.402
Nobody shrunk your shirts,

16:59.471 --> 17:01.638
nobody added steps
to the stairwell at home,

17:01.706 --> 17:04.273
and I am <i>certain</i>

17:04.342 --> 17:07.010
that nobody made the buttons
on your cellphone smaller.

17:07.078 --> 17:09.179
Marvin, you're fat.

17:09.246 --> 17:11.513
Fat, fat, fat!

17:11.582 --> 17:12.848
♪ Back home to me ♪

17:12.849 --> 17:14.584
♪ I'll wear your colors ♪

17:14.651 --> 17:17.653
♪ till you come back home
to me ♪

17:17.721 --> 17:19.188
I'm mouth McFadden,

17:19.189 --> 17:21.323
and we'll be right back
after this.

17:27.483 --> 17:28.483
That was totally uncalled for,
especially coming from

17:28.483 --> 17:29.750
the "0 is not a size"
model.

17:29.751 --> 17:31.419
Well, it's not a shape,
either,

17:31.487 --> 17:32.953
unless you're a doughnut.

17:32.954 --> 17:34.088
Where
is this coming from?

17:34.089 --> 17:35.490
From your waistline,
mostly,

17:35.491 --> 17:37.091
and a little from your ass.

17:37.159 --> 17:38.426
I am sorry, Marvin,

17:38.427 --> 17:39.994
but you've been criticizing
the dry cleaner

17:40.062 --> 17:42.463
and making crazy insinuations
about all kinds of things

17:42.531 --> 17:44.298
when the truth is
you've gained weight.

17:44.366 --> 17:45.665
Okay, so I gained
a little weight.

17:45.666 --> 17:47.100
You have gained
<i>a lot</i> of weight.

17:47.101 --> 17:48.368
Guys, can we work
this out later?

17:48.369 --> 17:49.503
You're on in 10 seconds.

17:49.504 --> 17:51.671
Marvin, you need to
acknowledge the fact

17:51.739 --> 17:53.373
that you have
a weight problem.

17:53.441 --> 17:54.807
Oh, don't worry,
Millicent.

17:54.808 --> 17:56.543
You've made that quite clear
to everyone.

17:56.610 --> 18:00.180
We're back in five,
four, three, two...

18:00.248 --> 18:02.181
For those of you
just tuning in,

18:02.249 --> 18:04.483
my co-host and,
may I add, girlfriend,

18:04.551 --> 18:08.054
just called me...
what were your exact words?

18:08.121 --> 18:09.522
Oh, that's right.
I remember.

18:09.523 --> 18:10.889
"Fat. Fat, fat, fat."

18:10.890 --> 18:13.459
Well, we here at "mouth
and Millie in the morning"

18:13.527 --> 18:15.627
would love to hear
what you think about this.

18:18.364 --> 18:20.666
I want you to imagine
a family in a kitchen,

18:20.733 --> 18:22.034
eating breakfast.

18:22.035 --> 18:24.002
The crane will move
the camera in, right?

18:24.070 --> 18:25.671
The director will stand
over here

18:25.738 --> 18:27.005
with the cinematographer

18:27.006 --> 18:28.607
in what's called
"video village."

18:28.675 --> 18:31.142
Let me guess... you're
the video village idiot?

18:31.210 --> 18:32.210
[ Laughter ]

18:32.211 --> 18:33.711
Okay, okay.

18:33.779 --> 18:36.280
Now let's use our imaginations
and invent a movie together.

18:36.347 --> 18:37.949
A movie with a dragon.

18:38.016 --> 18:39.283
Or a princess.

18:39.284 --> 18:40.685
To sacrifice
to the dragon.

18:40.686 --> 18:41.786
Okay, here we go.

18:41.787 --> 18:43.287
I like it.
A dragon and a princess.

18:43.288 --> 18:45.122
Now, you can't have those
without a castle,

18:45.190 --> 18:47.058
so we could build
a castle right here.

18:47.125 --> 18:48.559
It'd be a pretty
small castle.

18:48.560 --> 18:50.927
Well, it wouldn't
look small on-screen

18:50.995 --> 18:52.495
thanks to Hollywood magic.

18:52.496 --> 18:53.930
This isn't Hollywood.

18:53.931 --> 18:55.899
Well, wouldn't it
just be cheaper

18:55.967 --> 18:57.533
to fly to a real castle?

18:57.602 --> 18:59.903
No, because then you'd have to
deal with permits, visas...

18:59.971 --> 19:02.038
my dad says they only make
movies in Los Angeles

19:02.106 --> 19:03.673
and New York, anyways.

19:03.741 --> 19:06.609
Well, it's guys like your dad
who are killing my business!

19:06.676 --> 19:08.176
Julian.

19:15.018 --> 19:17.052
The truth is, kids,
I spend most of my time

19:17.120 --> 19:18.754
calling people
who hang up on me,

19:18.822 --> 19:20.322
talking to assistants
who won't even put me through

19:20.389 --> 19:21.889
to their bosses,

19:21.957 --> 19:25.893
just trying to find someone,
anyone, to fill up this stage

19:25.961 --> 19:27.895
so that I don't have to look
for a second job

19:27.963 --> 19:29.631
or sell one of my kids
on the black market.

19:29.698 --> 19:31.099
Okay!

19:31.100 --> 19:34.268
Um, who wants to go see
the box factory next door?

19:34.336 --> 19:35.469
They sell boxes!

19:35.470 --> 19:37.271
Okay, come on.
Let's go, guys.

19:38.940 --> 19:40.440
[ Clears throat ]

19:42.076 --> 19:44.244
All right.
Come on.

19:44.311 --> 19:46.579
Come on.

19:46.648 --> 19:50.183
I wanted to see the dragon
eat the princess.

19:54.287 --> 19:56.722
[ Mates of state's
"unless I'm led" plays ]

19:59.392 --> 20:03.762
Compliments to the chef.
Seriously, this is delicious.

20:03.829 --> 20:06.798
Thank you.

20:06.866 --> 20:08.467
If you're out here,
then who's...

20:12.805 --> 20:14.839
Dan.

20:17.342 --> 20:20.010
You looked like
you needed a little help.

20:22.548 --> 20:24.382
Unless you'd rather I go.

20:24.449 --> 20:29.153
♪ I can feel the air
pushing and pointing out ♪

20:29.221 --> 20:32.656
I need
a tuna melt on rye.

20:32.723 --> 20:35.158
♪ And it's not fair ♪

20:35.226 --> 20:40.664
♪ that I can't ride along
unless I'm led ♪

20:40.731 --> 20:42.065
[ Shower running ]

20:42.066 --> 20:44.867
So, I was thinking take-out
for dinner tonight.

20:44.935 --> 20:45.902
Clay:
Sounds good.

20:45.903 --> 20:47.204
Is there anything

20:47.205 --> 20:50.038
you can't eat
with the pills you're taking?

20:50.106 --> 20:51.173
[ Shower stops ]
Nope.

20:51.174 --> 20:52.808
Hey, have you heard
from Nathan?

20:52.875 --> 20:55.744
Yeah, he checked in from
the showcase in Belgrade.

20:55.812 --> 20:57.079
Said it was going nice.

20:57.080 --> 20:59.181
Sounds like he found
a few prospects.

20:59.249 --> 21:01.483
That's great!

21:01.551 --> 21:04.419
Oh, you still have
some shampoo in your hair.

21:04.486 --> 21:07.322
♪ Now I'm slipping
in your blind faith ♪

21:07.389 --> 21:09.890
♪ oh ♪

21:09.958 --> 21:13.194
♪ and I'm sleeping
in the wrong bed ♪

21:13.262 --> 21:15.096
That's Jude,
and that one's Davis.

21:15.163 --> 21:16.497
Oh, they're adorable!

21:16.498 --> 21:18.933
Lucky for them, they look
nothing like your dad.

21:19.000 --> 21:20.300
[ Laughter ]

21:20.301 --> 21:21.835
That's for sure.

21:21.902 --> 21:23.970
Did she mention
that those adorable boys

21:24.038 --> 21:25.872
are her inspiration
for Baker man?

21:25.940 --> 21:27.541
Oh.
That's true, dad.

21:27.609 --> 21:30.877
As a mom, I was frustrated
by the lack of options

21:30.945 --> 21:32.479
for
little boys' clothing.

21:32.547 --> 21:33.680
But as a designer,

21:33.681 --> 21:36.482
I noticed a huge gap
in the industry.

21:38.485 --> 21:40.353
I don't mean to impose,

21:40.420 --> 21:43.723
but my daughter Margot
loves your clothes,

21:43.790 --> 21:45.057
and I'll never
hear the end of it

21:45.058 --> 21:47.059
I don't come home with
an autograph.

21:47.127 --> 21:49.061
That's so sweet.
Of course.

21:51.365 --> 21:52.697
Margot?

21:52.698 --> 21:54.566
♪ You'll learn to live
without me ♪

21:54.634 --> 21:57.835
♪ oh, little girl,
pick up the pieces ♪

21:57.903 --> 22:00.171
♪ you'll learn to live
without me ♪

22:00.239 --> 22:03.141
Hey, you didn't want to go
to the box factory?

22:03.208 --> 22:05.109
Nah.
We were there last week.

22:09.080 --> 22:10.547
You know, dad and Clay

22:10.548 --> 22:13.317
had a hard time with
their agency at first.

22:13.385 --> 22:14.818
Yeah,
I'm starting to think

22:14.819 --> 22:16.687
this was just
one big bad idea.

22:16.755 --> 22:18.389
Come on. You're like
the farmer guy

22:18.456 --> 22:19.823
out in the middle
of nowhere

22:19.824 --> 22:22.192
who decided to build a baseball
field in his backyard.

22:22.294 --> 22:25.762
Everyone told him he was crazy,
but you know what?

22:25.829 --> 22:27.330
He built it anyway...

22:27.398 --> 22:29.799
all because he heard
a voice that said,

22:29.866 --> 22:31.768
"if you build it,
he will come."

22:31.835 --> 22:33.869
And you know what?

22:33.937 --> 22:35.371
He came.

22:35.372 --> 22:38.474
In fact...
Lots of people came.

22:40.576 --> 22:42.611
That's a pretty good story,
Jamie.

22:42.679 --> 22:45.146
I guess I just need to have
a little faith, huh?

22:45.214 --> 22:47.816
Well, the thing is...
That's actually a movie.

22:47.883 --> 22:49.384
You should
probably know that

22:49.452 --> 22:51.620
if you want to make it
in show business.

22:51.688 --> 22:54.022
[ Laughs ]

22:57.559 --> 22:59.026
Well, I have to say,

22:59.027 --> 23:01.462
you certainly have a way
with people.

23:01.530 --> 23:02.996
Thanks, dad.

23:02.997 --> 23:05.232
You were a huge hit.

23:05.300 --> 23:07.301
Well, I should probably get back
and close the deal.

23:07.369 --> 23:08.869
Of course.

23:09.404 --> 23:10.738
Mwah!

23:10.739 --> 23:12.306
We'll talk later?

23:12.373 --> 23:14.140
Mm-hmm.

23:14.208 --> 23:17.811
And, honey,
this day was perfect.

23:17.878 --> 23:20.046
Yeah.

23:26.016 --> 23:27.516
Cheeseburger, order up.

23:27.550 --> 23:29.685
People are
loving the burgers.

23:29.753 --> 23:31.019
Well, the secret
to a great burger

23:31.020 --> 23:32.286
is to flip them
only once or twice.

23:32.287 --> 23:33.521
That way,
you don't lose the juice.

23:33.522 --> 23:35.256
Trial and error.

23:35.324 --> 23:40.028
♪ Gone today
'cause it's hard to stay ♪

23:40.096 --> 23:43.464
♪ when the line is long ♪

23:43.532 --> 23:45.867
Well, that was quick.

23:45.935 --> 23:48.702
I'm seriously
not in the mood, Victoria.

23:48.770 --> 23:50.137
Let me guess.

23:50.138 --> 23:53.807
He got some bimbo
to impress some horny investors.

23:53.875 --> 23:55.375
Thanks, mom.

23:56.845 --> 23:58.445
Where are the boys?

23:58.512 --> 23:59.813
They're sleeping.

23:59.814 --> 24:01.915
I took
Judeâs temperature twice,

24:01.983 --> 24:04.984
and he doesn't have a fever,
but he has a runny nose.

24:07.054 --> 24:10.022
You know, I just wanted to
spend the day with him,

24:10.090 --> 24:12.859
and somehow,
even that was too much to ask.

24:12.926 --> 24:14.693
Is this where I give you
my sad face?

24:14.762 --> 24:15.828
Oh, please.

24:15.829 --> 24:17.529
We both know
you've botoxed away

24:17.597 --> 24:19.430
all remnants
of human emotion.

24:19.498 --> 24:21.566
Don't you take this
out on me.

24:21.634 --> 24:24.669
I tried to show you
who your father really is,

24:24.737 --> 24:28.306
and if he'd been around more,
this would not be a surprise.

24:28.374 --> 24:29.941
Point taken.

24:31.811 --> 24:34.412
I don't know.
I guess I just hoped...

24:34.480 --> 24:36.680
what?
That he could change?

24:36.748 --> 24:38.015
You did.

24:38.016 --> 24:41.652
Honey, that is
who the man is, okay?

24:41.719 --> 24:46.490
Despite all of his promises,
he has never changed,

24:46.557 --> 24:49.059
and he will never change.

24:49.127 --> 24:52.162
I guess we should give him
credit for being consistent.

24:52.229 --> 24:54.097
[ Scoffs ]

24:54.165 --> 24:56.365
I have to go.

24:56.433 --> 24:57.967
You're leaving?

24:58.035 --> 25:01.104
Back to New York.

25:01.172 --> 25:02.438
Wha...

25:02.439 --> 25:03.773
but why?

25:03.774 --> 25:07.375
Well, I can only take this town
in small doses.

25:08.945 --> 25:10.578
And as much as
I'm gonna miss the twins,

25:10.646 --> 25:14.716
you have your father
and your new business venture,

25:14.784 --> 25:17.719
and there's
nothing left for me to do.

25:17.787 --> 25:22.857
♪ In your dreams ♪

25:22.925 --> 25:24.125
[ Door closes ]

25:24.126 --> 25:25.927
[ Upbeat music plays ]

25:36.705 --> 25:39.272
[ Telephone ringing ]

25:41.209 --> 25:42.209
[ Music stops ]

25:42.210 --> 25:43.276
[ Ringing continues ]

25:43.277 --> 25:44.777
Don't hang up!

25:45.579 --> 25:48.648
Don't hang up!

25:48.716 --> 25:49.916
This is Julian Baker.

25:49.917 --> 25:51.718
Hi, Julian.
David Taylor.

25:51.785 --> 25:53.720
I'm calling
because it's my understanding

25:53.787 --> 25:56.188
that you might have some
stage space available.

25:56.256 --> 25:58.257
Yes, that's true.
I mean, not "might."

25:58.325 --> 25:59.925
I... I... I do.
It's available.

25:59.993 --> 26:02.761
We just received a late pick-up
for our television series

26:02.829 --> 26:05.097
and are interested in shooting
in Tree Hill.

26:05.165 --> 26:08.133
Well, we can definitely
accommodate a TV show here.

26:08.201 --> 26:10.802
I mean, in fact,
it's actually the perfect spot

26:10.870 --> 26:12.136
for a TV production.

26:12.137 --> 26:14.839
I hope so. How soon
can we see the space?

26:14.907 --> 26:17.708
Uh, let me see if I can
move some things around.

26:17.776 --> 26:20.078
Uh...

26:20.145 --> 26:22.180
Yeah, I can try
and clear my schedule

26:22.248 --> 26:24.648
for the end of the day
if that works for you.

26:24.716 --> 26:26.017
Perfect.

26:26.018 --> 26:27.817
We'll arrange for a stop-over
this afternoon.

26:27.886 --> 26:29.719
That sounds good.
Great.

26:29.787 --> 26:30.954
This afternoon.

26:30.955 --> 26:33.023
See you then.

26:33.091 --> 26:34.591
[ Receiver clicks ]

26:36.194 --> 26:38.128
Yes!

26:38.196 --> 26:39.763
Yes!!

26:46.536 --> 26:47.937
[ Glasses chime ]

26:47.938 --> 26:51.073
♪ Chris Keller, you sing so bad,
it's funny ♪

26:51.141 --> 26:53.075
♪ Chris Keller,
you write jingles for money ♪

26:53.143 --> 26:54.243
Yeah, yeah, okay.

26:54.244 --> 26:55.644
Like I told
your girlfriend...

26:55.645 --> 26:56.979
oh, sorry,
ex-girlfriend...

26:56.980 --> 26:58.247
that song pays my rent,

26:58.248 --> 27:00.081
which is a lot more
than a bartender makes.

27:00.149 --> 27:01.950
Bar <i>manager.</i>

27:03.852 --> 27:05.486
Look, man, I know
you're pissed at me,

27:05.554 --> 27:06.788
but you don't even know me.

27:06.789 --> 27:08.222
I'm not a bad guy.

27:08.223 --> 27:09.489
Maybe if you stopped
blaming me for getting dumped,

27:09.490 --> 27:10.824
you'd see that.

27:10.825 --> 27:14.694
How about I <i>pretend</i>
<i>to take your word for it</i>

27:14.762 --> 27:16.863
and <i>not</i> get to know you?

27:16.932 --> 27:18.332
Well, your loss.

27:18.333 --> 27:20.700
Chris Keller knows
some real nice girls

27:20.768 --> 27:22.769
that just might cure
what ails you.

27:32.379 --> 27:35.415
Yo, you got to admit,
this helps a guy feel better.

27:35.482 --> 27:37.116
Am I right?
Am I right?!

27:37.184 --> 27:38.418
[ Laughs ]

27:38.419 --> 27:40.319
<i>Male announcer:</i>
<i>You know her from</i>

27:40.386 --> 27:41.820
<i>"dirty dreams till Tuesday."</i>

27:41.821 --> 27:45.457
<i>Please welcome Alex du-me.</i>

27:45.524 --> 27:48.193
Alex du-me?

27:48.261 --> 27:50.528
[ Laughs ]

27:50.596 --> 27:51.796
That's awesome!

27:51.797 --> 27:53.631
Alex du-me!

27:59.204 --> 28:00.304
Perfect timing.
Hi.

28:00.305 --> 28:01.805
Tell me about it.

28:01.840 --> 28:04.108
I just got off the phone
with two TV producers from L.A.

28:04.176 --> 28:06.344
They're interested in filming
at the studios.

28:06.411 --> 28:07.411
Really?

28:07.412 --> 28:08.679
Yes, they are.

28:08.680 --> 28:10.247
They're flying in
from Atlanta today,

28:10.315 --> 28:13.116
and if they like what they see,
we can close the deal tonight.

28:13.184 --> 28:14.717
Well, how could they not?

28:14.785 --> 28:16.719
Boys,
your daddy's a genius.

28:16.787 --> 28:18.888
So, how did things go
with <i>your</i> father today?

28:18.956 --> 28:20.490
Did you
bogey down or what?

28:20.557 --> 28:21.691
Oh, not exactly.

28:21.692 --> 28:23.293
I think
he was more interested

28:23.361 --> 28:25.028
in showing me off
to his friends.

28:25.096 --> 28:26.929
Oh, I'm sorry, baby.

28:26.997 --> 28:28.497
It's okay.

28:28.531 --> 28:30.265
Listen, Judeâs gota bit
of a temperature.

28:30.333 --> 28:32.701
Do you think you have time
to drop Davis off at daycare

28:32.768 --> 28:34.203
on your way
back to the stages?

28:34.204 --> 28:35.404
Yeah,
if I go right now.

28:35.405 --> 28:36.705
Okay.

28:36.706 --> 28:38.107
The only thing worse
than one sick baby...

28:38.108 --> 28:39.841
Is two sick babies.

28:39.909 --> 28:42.511
You're my hero,
Julian Baker.

28:42.578 --> 28:43.844
Good luck today.

28:43.845 --> 28:45.946
I hope
you don't have to giggle

28:46.015 --> 28:48.282
and shake your ass
like I did.

28:48.350 --> 28:50.418
Hey, if it means
they'll use the stage,

28:50.486 --> 28:51.452
I'll do
whatever it takes.

28:51.453 --> 28:52.953
[ Chuckles ]

28:52.954 --> 28:56.891
Say, "bye, daddy.
Bye, daddy."

28:56.958 --> 29:00.994
[ The wooden birds' "be no lie"
plays ]

29:01.062 --> 29:06.099
♪ I am your ivory comb,
I've counted every curl ♪

29:06.167 --> 29:11.638
♪ every curl,
every curl, every curl ♪

29:11.705 --> 29:13.373
[ Camera shutter clicking ]

29:13.441 --> 29:18.411
♪ I'll be the bread you take,
so take it easy, girl ♪

29:18.478 --> 29:24.450
♪ easy, girl,
easy, girl, easy, girl ♪

29:24.518 --> 29:26.052
Hi, mom.
Hi, honey.

29:26.119 --> 29:27.819
Mwah.
Grandpa Dan!

29:27.887 --> 29:30.456
♪ I wonder what you'd do... ♪

29:30.524 --> 29:33.791
What are you doing here?

29:33.859 --> 29:36.094
Just helping
your mom out. Oh!

29:36.162 --> 29:37.895
You want to join?
Sure.

29:37.963 --> 29:39.597
Excuse me.
Is that Dan Scott?

29:39.665 --> 29:40.965
Yeah.

29:40.966 --> 29:42.800
How could you allow
that man to work for you,

29:42.868 --> 29:44.102
to be around
your children?

29:44.103 --> 29:45.570
Excuse me?

29:45.571 --> 29:47.071
He's a murderer!

29:47.138 --> 29:50.941
♪ And they burn and they burn ♪

29:53.644 --> 29:56.146
I really don't think
that's any of your business.

29:56.214 --> 29:59.649
Oh, yes, it is, especially
if he's cooking our food.

29:59.717 --> 30:02.018
Haley.

30:02.087 --> 30:03.886
It's okay.

30:03.954 --> 30:05.955
I'll leave.

30:06.022 --> 30:07.856
I'll see you
back at the house.

30:07.924 --> 30:09.424
No.

30:10.527 --> 30:12.395
You should stay.

30:12.463 --> 30:15.465
If anyone here has a problem
with this man cooking your food,

30:15.532 --> 30:17.333
you're welcome
to go someplace else.

30:17.401 --> 30:18.568
We will.

30:18.569 --> 30:19.867
All right, then.

30:19.868 --> 30:21.703
Your food
is on the house today.

30:21.770 --> 30:23.238
Now get out.

30:23.239 --> 30:29.211
♪ Into the fire,
into the fire, into the fire ♪

30:29.278 --> 30:35.149
♪ into the fire,
into the fire, into the fire ♪

30:35.217 --> 30:39.920
♪ into the fire,
into the fire, into the fire ♪

30:46.925 --> 30:47.925
I asked her to move in.
I was <i>so</i> romantic.

30:47.926 --> 30:50.394
And then
just out of the blue,

30:50.462 --> 30:53.030
she just leaves me
for her <i>music!</i>

30:53.098 --> 30:55.366
Aw, baby.
I'm so sorry.

30:55.433 --> 30:57.001
That's terrible.

30:57.068 --> 30:59.168
<i>Next up on the main stage</i>

30:59.236 --> 31:01.004
<i>is the pony express.</i>

31:01.071 --> 31:04.173
Well, sweet cheeks,
that's my cue.

31:04.241 --> 31:06.309
This one's on the house.

31:06.377 --> 31:09.112
[ Chuckles ]

31:09.179 --> 31:11.414
[ Sighs ]

31:11.482 --> 31:14.984
Thank you, pony.

31:15.051 --> 31:16.552
You used my pain
for a free lap dance.

31:16.620 --> 31:17.920
Aw, come on, man.

31:17.921 --> 31:19.421
It's a good story,
and you're not using it.

31:19.489 --> 31:20.890
Glad
you're enjoying yourself.

31:20.891 --> 31:21.891
I'm out of here.

31:21.892 --> 31:22.658
No, no, no.
Okay, okay.

31:22.659 --> 31:24.159
L-look, look, look.

31:24.193 --> 31:26.161
I won't use your sad-sack story
to pick up strippers, okay?

31:26.229 --> 31:28.597
But look, seriously,
you haven't asked my opinion,

31:28.665 --> 31:29.932
but all B.S. Aside,

31:29.933 --> 31:32.000
she would have left you
sooner or later.

31:32.067 --> 31:34.301
You don't know that!
You don't even know Alex.

31:34.369 --> 31:36.437
Actually, I do,
and trust me...

31:36.539 --> 31:37.639
it's in her DNA.

31:37.640 --> 31:39.140
Alex is an artist.

31:39.141 --> 31:42.810
Some of us need constant
validation and appreciation.

31:42.878 --> 31:46.447
I gave her validation
and appreciation all the time.

31:46.515 --> 31:47.548
Like 24/7.

31:47.549 --> 31:48.615
See,
and she still left.

31:48.616 --> 31:49.816
That's my point.

31:49.817 --> 31:53.219
No one person or town
can fill the void.

31:53.287 --> 31:54.787
That...

31:57.158 --> 32:00.393
That girl
is <i>never</i> gonna settle down.

32:00.461 --> 32:01.762
Trust me.

32:01.763 --> 32:07.332
Like I said,
you don't know her.

32:07.400 --> 32:09.268
[ Sighs ]

32:09.335 --> 32:13.806
I knew she'd take that tour.

32:18.244 --> 32:23.181
The state of north Carolina
offers a generous tax incentive.

32:23.248 --> 32:24.983
[ Cellphone rings ]

32:29.388 --> 32:30.388
[ Cellphone beeps ]

32:30.389 --> 32:31.722
Yeah, this is Julian.

32:31.723 --> 32:34.158
Hi, this is Amy calling
from David Taylor's office.

32:34.226 --> 32:35.626
Their flight landed early,

32:35.627 --> 32:37.628
and they'd like to
meet with you directly.

32:37.696 --> 32:38.996
Will that be a problem?

32:38.997 --> 32:40.497
No.
No, no, no.

32:40.532 --> 32:42.499
Not... absolutely.
I'll be there.

32:42.567 --> 32:44.201
Um, okay, great.
Thanks.

32:44.268 --> 32:45.768
[ Cellphone beeps ]

32:47.705 --> 32:50.407
In addition, the company
has recently invested

32:50.475 --> 32:52.942
in state-of-the-art equipment,
which will...

32:53.010 --> 32:54.578
there we go.

32:56.147 --> 32:58.680
[ Brooke Annibale's
"yours and mine" plays ]

32:58.748 --> 33:00.248
Haley.

33:01.518 --> 33:03.252
I just want to
say thanks.

33:03.320 --> 33:04.487
Yeah.

33:04.488 --> 33:05.787
Well, she was wrong,
you know?

33:05.788 --> 33:06.888
You shouldn't have had to
deal with that.

33:06.889 --> 33:09.358
I did the crime.

33:09.426 --> 33:11.693
Doesn't mean you have to get
hammered for it all the time.

33:11.761 --> 33:13.562
♪ I'll be the chorus ♪

33:13.630 --> 33:16.564
♪ you be the verse ♪

33:16.632 --> 33:20.602
♪ we'll live in a forest
of beautiful words ♪

33:20.669 --> 33:23.671
♪ I'll be the strings ♪

33:23.739 --> 33:25.607
[ Knock on door ]
♪ you be the keys ♪

33:25.674 --> 33:28.209
♪ together we'll find
all the... ♪

33:28.277 --> 33:29.544
Hi.

33:29.545 --> 33:31.111
What are you doing here?

33:31.179 --> 33:33.113
Good news should never be shared
over the phone.

33:33.181 --> 33:36.350
♪ All we've got
is all we have... ♪

33:36.417 --> 33:38.585
Baker man
officially has funding...

33:38.653 --> 33:41.455
actually,
full financial backing.

33:41.523 --> 33:43.524
But they haven't seen
a single design.

33:43.591 --> 33:44.824
Doesn't matter.

33:44.825 --> 33:46.626
They want to work
with the designer.

33:46.693 --> 33:49.228
That's great.

33:49.296 --> 33:51.397
Well, you don't seem
very happy about it.

33:51.465 --> 33:52.865
No, dad.

33:52.866 --> 33:56.335
I'm... I'm thrilled that
they want to invest in the line.

33:56.403 --> 33:57.603
Thank you.

33:57.604 --> 34:00.005
♪ And we'll have everything ♪

34:00.073 --> 34:02.641
[ Sighs ] Well...

34:02.708 --> 34:04.242
But you're upset with me.

34:04.310 --> 34:06.844
Well...

34:06.912 --> 34:08.547
[ Sighs ]

34:08.614 --> 34:10.081
I never get to see you.

34:10.081 --> 34:12.784
And I showed up today
thinking that you and I

34:12.851 --> 34:15.387
were gonna spend a day
on the golf course,

34:15.454 --> 34:16.954
just the two of us.

34:18.989 --> 34:20.558
That would have been nice.

34:20.625 --> 34:23.194
But do you mean that?

34:23.261 --> 34:25.795
Well, of course I do.

34:25.862 --> 34:28.831
I would love to spend time
with you

34:28.900 --> 34:31.967
and my two handsome grandsons,
and we will, I promise.

34:32.036 --> 34:33.536
I'll be back in town
more often now,

34:33.572 --> 34:35.036
thanks to Baker man,

34:35.038 --> 34:37.739
but, honey, you came to me
with a business proposal.

34:37.808 --> 34:39.308
I know that.

34:39.342 --> 34:40.976
And with opportunities
like this,

34:41.043 --> 34:42.945
you have to strike
while the iron is hot,

34:43.013 --> 34:44.513
and that's
what we did today.

34:44.514 --> 34:45.748
Because of that,

34:45.748 --> 34:48.284
we'll have our day
on the golf course,

34:48.351 --> 34:49.885
just the two of us.

34:49.953 --> 34:52.821
♪ Your hand ♪

34:52.888 --> 34:55.757
For now, I have a flight
to catch back to L.A.,

34:55.824 --> 34:58.327
and you have a clothing line
to design.

34:58.394 --> 35:01.597
You handled yourself
like a total pro today.

35:01.664 --> 35:02.964
♪ So what I have not... ♪

35:02.965 --> 35:04.966
And I'm so proud of you.

35:05.034 --> 35:11.839
♪ ...I fill in with what
you got, and we'll be okay ♪

35:11.906 --> 35:16.310
♪ take yours and mine,
we'll combine ♪

35:16.378 --> 35:19.079
Excuse me.
I'm looking for a nice scotch.

35:19.147 --> 35:21.982
I want something aged
like 12, 15 years.

35:22.050 --> 35:23.650
Any particular brand?

35:23.718 --> 35:26.686
Uh, red label, blue label,
black label, I don't know.

35:26.754 --> 35:28.821
What happened to six-pack
versus keg?

35:28.889 --> 35:32.726
[ Chuckles ]
How about this?

35:32.793 --> 35:34.293
Yeah.

35:38.698 --> 35:40.198
Hey.

35:42.034 --> 35:43.534
What's wrong?

35:44.771 --> 35:45.971
I saw you.

35:45.972 --> 35:47.939
You saw what?
What's the matter?

35:48.007 --> 35:49.808
I saw you
buying drugs, Clay.

35:49.876 --> 35:52.244
You've been lying to me
this entire time.

35:52.312 --> 35:53.979
Lying to you? Quinn,
what are you talking about?

35:54.046 --> 35:55.045
I didn't buy any drugs.

35:55.046 --> 35:56.347
Don't lie to me anymore!

35:56.348 --> 35:57.582
I was there!

35:57.583 --> 35:59.183
Maybe you saw something,
but it wasn't me.

35:59.251 --> 36:01.819
There are pictures!
I took pictures with my camera!

36:01.887 --> 36:03.154
This is crazy.

36:03.155 --> 36:04.622
You're acting crazy.
You realize that, right?

36:04.623 --> 36:05.990
What's wrong with you?

36:05.991 --> 36:07.392
What's wrong with <i>me?!</i>

36:07.393 --> 36:08.793
What's wrong
with <i>you,</i> Clay?!

36:08.794 --> 36:11.261
No wonder you need to
pick up your prescription,

36:11.329 --> 36:12.562
because you're not sick!

36:12.563 --> 36:14.063
You had
other pills to pick up!

36:20.204 --> 36:21.704
It's not like
it's a problem.

36:21.739 --> 36:22.906
You fooled me.

36:22.907 --> 36:24.808
You fooled me
into feeling sorry for you,

36:24.875 --> 36:27.443
and I stayed awake,
and I worried sick about you!

36:27.511 --> 36:28.678
How could you?!
Quinn, wait!

36:28.679 --> 36:29.345
No!

36:29.346 --> 36:30.846
Quinn!

36:45.228 --> 36:48.096
This guy says he's faced this kind
of discrimination his whole life,

36:48.164 --> 36:50.599
and watching me endure it
literally hurt his heart.

36:50.667 --> 36:52.735
Yeah, I'm sure
it has nothing to do

36:52.802 --> 36:55.237
with the carton of twinkie
she eats every day.

36:56.573 --> 36:58.073
Fine.

37:00.476 --> 37:04.479
I was unprofessional and rude,
and for that, I apologize.

37:04.546 --> 37:06.381
Now, is that so hard?
Thank you.

37:06.448 --> 37:07.948
Marvin,
I am not finished.

37:07.983 --> 37:10.150
What you need to understand

37:10.218 --> 37:12.754
is that it came
from a place of love.

37:12.821 --> 37:14.655
[ Voice breaking ]
I am genuinely concerned

37:14.723 --> 37:16.757
for your health.

37:16.824 --> 37:19.626
And I'm sorry
if I hurt your feelings,

37:19.694 --> 37:21.561
but I am not
gonna sit here

37:21.629 --> 37:24.063
and watch you
eat yourself to death.

37:33.807 --> 37:36.375
I went to the ATM
to get money for a taxi,

37:36.443 --> 37:37.777
and I found this.

37:37.778 --> 37:40.746
It's her room key.
She lived in a hotel.

37:40.814 --> 37:42.615
Should have known better.

37:42.682 --> 37:44.216
And who lives in hotels?

37:44.284 --> 37:46.351
People whose stay
is temporary.

37:46.420 --> 37:48.219
You never had a chance,
my friend.

37:48.287 --> 37:49.787
Two more!

37:51.189 --> 37:54.526
Had nothing to do
with you, though.

37:54.593 --> 37:57.995
Just so you know,
I still don't like you.

37:58.063 --> 37:59.564
I'll drink to that.

38:02.301 --> 38:04.401
[ Other lives' "tamer animals"
plays ]

38:28.659 --> 38:30.860
Would you like to begin
your special tasting session,

38:30.928 --> 38:32.095
Mr. McFadden?

38:32.096 --> 38:33.563
Or would you prefer
to continue waiting?

38:33.564 --> 38:37.333
Uh, no, I... I think
it's just me this evening.

38:37.434 --> 38:38.934
Ah.

38:41.237 --> 38:44.006
[ Sighs ]

38:44.074 --> 38:48.210
♪ Solitary motion ♪

38:48.278 --> 38:53.814
♪ in the wake
of an avalanche ♪

38:53.882 --> 38:58.919
♪ deer in the headlights ♪

38:58.988 --> 39:02.623
♪ there goes a weaker one ♪

39:04.659 --> 39:06.260
♪ he's listenin'
in the fast gaze... ♪

39:06.328 --> 39:08.095
When I was recovering
from the shooting,

39:08.162 --> 39:11.865
I was taking those pills
for the pain.

39:11.932 --> 39:13.766
And the prescription
ran out.

39:17.838 --> 39:19.606
I am so sorry.

39:23.211 --> 39:26.112
I was just so embarrassed
about it, and...

39:32.352 --> 39:33.886
and I'm sorry.

39:33.953 --> 39:35.453
♪ And it's always
troubling ♪

39:38.525 --> 39:40.992
♪ to keep it in
the hot Lane ♪

39:42.995 --> 39:46.031
♪ I don't care
about no scenery ♪

39:46.098 --> 39:50.435
♪ and you run from it then,
now you can't escape ♪

39:50.503 --> 39:52.003
Thanks again, Dan...
I really don't think

39:52.071 --> 39:54.339
that I could have made it
through today without you.

39:54.407 --> 39:56.206
Oh, I'm sure you would have
found a way.

39:59.044 --> 40:00.810
Besides, I enjoyed it.

40:03.048 --> 40:05.015
If you want me
to come in tomorrow,

40:05.082 --> 40:06.516
it's really no trouble.

40:06.517 --> 40:09.819
No, I don't think
that's such a good idea.

40:12.389 --> 40:15.324
Dan, it's not because
of that lady

40:15.392 --> 40:17.160
or any
of the other customers.

40:17.227 --> 40:19.328
It's just...

40:19.396 --> 40:21.630
This is Karen's café.

40:24.200 --> 40:27.036
♪ We're just tamer animals ♪

40:30.974 --> 40:34.142
[ Siren wails ]

40:39.782 --> 40:41.449
Hey, baby.

40:41.516 --> 40:42.784
Hey,
is everything okay?

40:42.785 --> 40:43.718
Yeah, why?

40:43.719 --> 40:44.986
Well,
the daycare called

40:44.987 --> 40:46.788
and said you never
dropped Davis off.

40:49.592 --> 40:52.392
♪ Trying to see
if you hold it in ♪

40:52.460 --> 40:56.630
♪ and you run from it then,
now you can't escape ♪

40:56.698 --> 41:00.601
♪ 'cause it's all you see ♪

41:00.668 --> 41:04.437
♪ but we're all just an end
to a simple thing ♪

41:04.505 --> 41:08.040
♪ and it's all you see ♪

41:08.108 --> 41:13.713
♪ and it's all you see ♪

